The official Linear MCP server is a centrally hosted, managed interface designed to connect AI models like Claude and Cursor to Linear data [1]. It supports OAuth 2.1 authentication and Streamable HTTP transports at the endpoint https://mcp.linear.app/mcp [1].

To use it in a compatible client, add the server using the following configuration [1]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "linear": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "https://mcp.linear.app/mcp"]
    }
  }
}
```

Beyond the official server, several community-maintained alternatives exist for specific use cases, such as the lsmc-bio/linear-mcp server, which provides more comprehensive support for Linear hierarchies like initiatives, milestones, and workspace-wide search [2].
